  "text": "Related work also indicated that Chinese drivers are more likely to be open towards a functionality solely because it is new, while Germans prioritize practicability (H6) [CITATION_1] . From our focus groups we learnt to expect that participants who stress the importance of transparency are often sceptic towards sharing personal data (H7) and that users are more open towards sharing their personal emotion detection data after they experienced a demonstration of its benefits (H8).",
